Did you know that ENS is not confined to Ethereum addresses? It can actually map to any arbitrary data, allowing users to associate their ENS names with other cryptocurrency addresses, IPFS hashes, and more. This interoperability potential makes ENS a versatile tool beyond the Ethereum network.

Did you know that ENS (Ethereum Name Service) supports a concept known as subdomains? Owners of a primary ENS domain can create unlimited subdomains under it and set different rules or owners for each. This allows for a structure within a single domain to delegate control over different subs in a decentralized manner.
